        <name xml:lang="en">hard coal</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Input of coal for the production of hydrogen via gasification. This value is deduced from the data provided by Li, J. et al. (2022): "The carbon footprint and cost of coal-based hydrogen production with and without carbon capture and storage technology in China, Journal of Cleaner Production, 362, 132514". Namely, they reported that the production of 1 kg of hydrogen from coal requires to mine 8.9 kg of coal, which is subsequently treated leading to the wastage of 2.04 kg. An additional 0.089 kg of coal are lost during transport to the hydrogen production facility. </comment>
