        <name xml:lang="en">hard coal ash</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">This value is estimated based on the input of anthracite (hard coal) and an average ash content of 11% to ensure the mass balance and the completeness of the dataset. Besides, the chemical composition of anthracite comprise of around 77% carbon, 6-16% ash, and moister. Some trace elements are also present in the chemical composition of anthracite, such as sulfur − 0.23-1.2%, silica oxide − 2.2-5.4%, alumina − 2%, ferric oxide − 0.4%. Reference: Wypych, George. "Fillers–Origin, chemical composition, properties, and morphology." Handbook of Fillers 4 (266) (2016): 13.</comment>
