      <intermediateExchange id="43b0a762-8852-55d9-8473-3eabd921f364" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="000067-56-1" amount="2.785335055014414E-05" intermediateExchangeId="4a0b47d3-c643-4b67-841b-b5689787f7a1" activityLinkId="2a8c2e77-976c-5fb1-b68c-cb3a7093129e">
        <name xml:lang="en">methanol</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Methanol used as a solvent in the acid gas removal system which recovers hydrogen sulfide and carbon dioxide as separate streams. The Rectisol® process develped by Linde and Lurgi, is a physical acid gas removal process that can purify synthesis gas down to 0.1 ppm total sulfur, including hydrogen sulfide (H2S) and carbonyl sulfide (COS), and carbon dioxide (CO2) in the ppm range. It is also able to remove impurities such as hydrocarbons, ammonia, and hydrogen cyanide, consistent with its origin as a treatment for syngas from the Lurgi gasifier which contains these kinds of impurities.  Value reported by Li, J. et al. (2022): "The carbon footprint and cost of coal-based hydrogen production with and without carbon capture and storage technology in China, Journal of Cleaner Production, 362, 132514" for the production of hydrogen via coal gasification.</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="2.785335055014414E-05" mu="-10.488557291820317" variance="0.006" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.0112"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="2" completeness="4" temporalCorrelation="1" geographicalCorrelation="5" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="2"/>
        </uncertainty>
