        <name xml:lang="en">water, deionised</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Raw surface water input for steam production, with demineralisation. This value is deduced from the input of pure water for the production of hydrogen via coal gasification. Namely, an amount of 10.5 kg pure water input per kg H2 produced was reported by  Li, J. et al. (2022): "The carbon footprint and cost of coal-based hydrogen production with and without carbon capture and storage technology in China, Journal of Cleaner Production, 362, 132514", while 4.51 kg of steam were also cogenerated. Based on the latter consideration, the total input of deionised water is 5.99 kg.</comment>
