      <elementaryExchange id="3ecdb88c-0e9f-52f0-bf79-f63301701889" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" amount="5.222697846038425E-05" isCalculatedAmount="true" mathematicalRelation="(734000 / 845000 )*SO2" elementaryExchangeId="c1b91234-6f24-417b-8309-46111d09c457" formula="NOx">
        <name xml:lang="en">Nitrogen oxides</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Due to the absence of process data for the release of NOx for the production of hydrogen from coal, this exchange was roughly estimated as described below.

In the United States, an amount of 734,000 t of NOx emissions were released in 2022, along with 845,000 t of SO2. Assuming that the release of NOx and SO2 is correlated, this ratio was here used as a rough estimation, to approximate the release in NOx for the production of hydrogen from coal.

References: 
https://www.epa.gov/power-sector/progress-report-emissions-reductions#so2
https://www.epa.gov/power-sector/progress-report-emissions-reductions#nox</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="5.222697846038425E-05" mu="-9.859911367842663" variance="0.04" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.04380000000000001"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="2" completeness="3" temporalCorrelation="1" geographicalCorrelation="5" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="2"/>
